{ Welcome to another instructive study by NoseKnowsAll. This study is a first look at the Caro-Kann variation for black, compiled by members of the ChessDojo Training Program. To join the program itself (and join a community of chess players of all levels looking to improve their classical chess), check out: https://www.chessdojo.club. Trying the program is absolutely free, and there are thousands of members looking to spar these positions with you!

This study is designed for lichess players rated below 2000. It is organized into 6 sections, each representing a key variation of the Caro-Kann.

Each section consists of the following:
- Key variations to know as well as basic middle game plans for each side
- Sparring position(s) -- Spar a friend from this position to better understand the middlegame strategy
- Common traps -- Treat these as puzzles and try to solve them for yourself before reading the text
- Model games -- These demonstrate the plans discussed in the key variations file

The emphasis is on understanding, not memorizing!

Feel free to watch the companion video as well: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z7C-zJwNG54 }
 *


