1. e4 c6 2. Bc4? d5 3. Bb3 { It is my understanding that Simon Williams was drunk in the pub the day before and challenged someone to come up with a cheeky opening he should play against Gawain Jones in the next round. He went with the Hillbilly attack, and Gawain Jones prefectly refuted it: } 3... dxe4 4. Qh5 g6 5. Qh4 Bg7 6. Nc3 a5!? (6... Nf6!? $15 { Would transpose directly into our main line. Note how unconcerned Gawain is with holding onto the extra pawn in the game. }) 7. Nxe4 a4 8. Bc4 b5 9. Be2 { While black's moves look a bit odd, they've successfully pushed the LSB to the silly e2 square without losing a single tempo. Black now has a lead in development. } 9... Nh6 10. g4?! a3! 11. Rb1 Qd5! 12. Nc3 Qxh1 { By this point, it should be clear that white is busted. } 13. Kf1 Be5 14. Bf3 Qxh2 15. Nh3 Nxg4 16. Bxg4 Bf6 $19 { 0-1 Black wins. } 0-1


